#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/earthdistance.xml:142(para)
msgid "The second part of the module relies on representing Earth locations as values of type <type>point</type>, in which the first component is taken to represent longitude in degrees, and the second component is taken to represent latitude in degrees. Points are taken as (longitude, latitude) and not vice versa because longitude is closer to the intuitive idea of x-axis and latitude to y-axis."
